@book{kolar2000,
  ABSTRACT = {The aim of this work is threefold: first it should be a monographical work on natural bundles and natural operators in differential geometry. This is a field which every differential geometer has met several times, but which is not treated in detail in one place. Let us explain a little, what we mean by naturality. Exterior derivative commutes with the pullback of differential forms. In the background of this statement are the following general concepts. The vector bundle $\bigwedge ^k (T^* M)$ is in fact the value of a functor, which associates a bundle over $M$ to each manifold $M$ and a vector bundle homomorphism over $f$ to each local diffeomorphism $f$ between manifolds of the same dimension. This is a simple example of the concept of a natural bundle. The fact that exterior derivative $d$ transforms sections of $\bigwedge ^k (T^* M)$ into sections of $\bigwedge^{k+1} (T^* M)$ for every manifold $M$ can be expressed by saying that $d$ is an operator from $\bigwedge^{k} (T^* M)$ into $\bigwedge^{k+1} (T^* M)$.},
